aster,' said Dr Alexander steadily looking ahead, 'because the wrestle-cap of the lower slammer is what they call muckling. If you will put your hand into my right hand pocket, Professor, you will find some cigarettes.'

'I am a non-smoker,' said Krug. 'And anyway I do not believe there are any there.'

They drove on for some time in silence.

'Why?' asked Dr Alexander, gently treading, gently releasing.

'A passing thought,' said Krug.

